public class ClassInfo

Method Detail

isAncestorOf

public static void isAncestorOf(java.lang.String ancestor,
                                java.lang.String child)
Tests whether a class is an ancestor of another class. This method prints "t" to standard out if the class is an ancestor of the other class. If the class is not an ancestor or either class cannot be found, this method prints nil to standard out.

Parameters:
ancestor - Name of the ancestor class
child - Name of the supposed child class

getClassInfo

public static void getClassInfo(java.lang.String className)
Gets information on the specified class. Information is returned as a list of lists that is printed to System.out.

Parameters:
className - a String value

getClassInfo

public static void getClassInfo(java.lang.String className,
                                java.lang.String[] imports)
Looks up an unqualified class name in the class path to find possible fully qualified matches.

Parameters:
className - a value of type 'String'
imports - an array of imported packages

hasMember

public static void hasMember(java.lang.String className,
                             java.lang.String memberName)
Tests whether a class has a member of a specified name. If so, prints t to standard out; if not, nil.

Parameters:
className - Name of class
memberName - Name of member
